cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their coverage problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes a homology-based distributed algorithm for coverage hole detection. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper uses algebraic objects to address coverage problems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for coverage hole detection. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with a network of sensors working together to detect coverage holes.
